This was legal code in 0.8.2

```TypeScript
declare module foo {
    export function(): string;
    export var x: number; 
}
var d = foo();
var e = foo.x;
```
so was this code

```TypeScript
declare module foo {
    export function new(): string;
    export var x: number; 
}
var d = new foo(); // this is not an error, but should be
var e = foo.x;
var f = foo.new(); // this is an error, but shouldnâ€™t be
```
In current develop branch this is broken, though this is according to the spec, this would be a breaking change for existing typescript code. We should allow this code to work as is for now and fix this behaviour with other breaking change
